stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 1: Understanding Your Nervous System) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (The Autonomic Nervous System) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (Your autonomic nervous system \(ANS\) operates automatically, controlling heart rate,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (breathing, digestion, and stress responses. It has two main branches plus an important) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (newer discovery:) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 600.4 Td (Sympathetic: Fight or Flight) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 584.4 Td (- Activated by perceived threat \(real or imagined\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 570.4 Td (- Heart rate increases, breathing quickens) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 556.4 Td (- Muscles tense, pupils dilate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 542.4 Td (- Digestion shuts down, energy mobilized) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.4 Td (- Feelings: Anxiety, panic, anger, hypervigilance) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 500.6 Td (Parasympathetic: Rest and Digest) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 484.6 Td (- Activated when safe and relaxed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 470.6 Td (- Heart rate slows, breathing deepens) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 456.6 Td (- Digestion resumes, repair processes activate) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 442.6 Td (- Feelings: Calm, connected, present, content) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 414.8 Td (Dorsal Vagal: Freeze/Shutdown) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 398.8 Td (- Activated when threat feels inescapable) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 384.8 Td (- Energy collapses, numbness, disconnection) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 370.8 Td (- Feelings: Hopelessness, dissociation, depression, exhaustion) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 341.0 Td (Polyvagal Theory: The Three States) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 323.0 Td (Dr. Stephen Porges' Polyvagal Theory explains how our nervous system constantly scans for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 309.0 Td (safety \(neuroception\) and moves between three states:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 295.0 Td (- Ventral Vagal \(safe/social\): Ideal state. Connected, calm, curious, creative.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 281.0 Td (- Sympathetic \(mobilized\): Fight or flight. Anxious, angry, restless.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 267.0 Td (- Dorsal Vagal \(immobilized\): Freeze or collapse. Numb, disconnected, shut down.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 237.2 Td (The Vagus Nerve) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 219.2 Td (The vagus nerve is the longest cranial nerve, connecting brain to gut. It is the main) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 205.2 Td (nerve of the parasympathetic system. Higher vagal tone = better ability to return to calm) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 191.2 Td (after stress.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 163.4 Td (Signs of Good Vagal Tone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 147.4 Td (- Quick recovery after stress) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 133.4 Td (- Good digestion) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 119.4 Td (- Healthy heart rate variability) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 105.4 Td (- Ability to socially engage) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 91.4 Td (- Emotional resilience) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
