stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 3: Vagus Nerve Activation Exercises) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 680.2 Td (These exercises directly stimulate the vagus nerve to shift from sympathetic/dorsal states) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 666.2 Td (toward ventral vagal \(safe and social\).) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 636.4 Td (1. Physiological Sigh \(fastest reset\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 618.4 Td (- Double inhale through nose \(short-short\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604.4 Td (- Long slow exhale through mouth) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 590.4 Td (- Repeat 3-5 times) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 576.4 Td (- Works within 1-2 breaths for acute anxiety) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 546.6 Td (2. Cold Water Vagal Dive Reflex) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 528.6 Td (- Splash cold water on face \(especially forehead and cheeks\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 514.6 Td (- Or: Hold ice cubes in hands for 30-60 seconds) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 500.6 Td (- Or: Cold water at end of shower for 30 seconds) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 486.6 Td (- Triggers automatic parasympathetic response) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 456.8 Td (3. Humming, Singing, and Gargling) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.8 Td (- Hum deeply for 2-3 minutes \(vibrates vagus nerve in throat\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 424.8 Td (- Sing loudly \(especially low notes\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 410.8 Td (- Gargle water vigorously for 30 seconds) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 396.8 Td (- Chant 'om' or 'voo' sound) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 367.0 Td (4. Extended Exhale Breathing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 349.0 Td (- Inhale for 4 counts) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 335.0 Td (- Exhale for 6-8 counts \(longer exhale activates PNS\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 321.0 Td (- Continue for 5-10 minutes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 307.0 Td (- Box breathing: 4 in, 4 hold, 4 out, 4 hold) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 277.2 Td (5. Orienting to Safety) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 259.2 Td (- Slowly look around your environment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 245.2 Td (- Name 5 things you can see) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 231.2 Td (- Name 4 things you can touch/feel) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 217.2 Td (- Name 3 things you can hear) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 203.2 Td (- This tells your nervous system: 'I am safe right now') Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 173.4 Td (6. Social Engagement) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 155.4 Td (- Make eye contact with a safe person) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 141.4 Td (- Listen to or use a warm, melodic voice tone) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 127.4 Td (- Smile \(even forced smiling sends safety signals\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 113.4 Td (- Hug or gentle touch from trusted person) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
