BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Chapter 6: Lifestyle for Nervous System Health) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 674.2 Td (Daily Practices for Regulation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.2 Td (- Morning: Sunlight within 30 min \(sets circadian rhythm, calms NS\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.2 Td (- Movement: Daily gentle exercise \(walking, yoga, swimming\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.2 Td (- Nature: Time outdoors \(proven to shift to parasympathetic\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 614.2 Td (- Connection: At least one meaningful interaction daily) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.2 Td (- Breathwork: 5-10 minutes of intentional breathing) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 586.2 Td (- Sleep: Consistent schedule, 7-9 hours) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 556.4 Td (Nutrition for the Nervous System) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 538.4 Td (- Omega-3 fats: Brain and nerve health \(fatty fish, walnuts\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 524.4 Td (- Magnesium: Natural relaxant \(leafy greens, dark chocolate\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.4 Td (- B vitamins: Nerve function \(whole grains, eggs\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 496.4 Td (- Probiotics: Gut-brain axis support \(fermented foods\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 482.4 Td (- Avoid: Excess caffeine, alcohol, sugar \(all dysregulating\)) Tj ET
