100 0 obj
<< /Length 3010 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (Frequently Asked Questions) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Q: How long does it take to regulate a dysregulated nervous system?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 660.2 Td (It varies greatly depending on how long dysregulation has been present. Some people notice) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 646.2 Td (shifts within days of consistent practice. Deeper changes take months of daily work. Be) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 632.2 Td (patient and consistent.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 604.4 Td (Q: Is this the same as anxiety?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 588.4 Td (Anxiety is often a symptom of nervous system dysregulation \(stuck in sympathetic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.4 Td (activation\). Regulation tools address the root cause rather than just managing symptoms.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 546.6 Td (Q: Can trauma cause nervous system dysregulation?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.6 Td (Yes. Trauma is one of the primary causes. The nervous system can get 'stuck' in protective) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 516.6 Td (states long after danger has passed. Professional trauma therapy combined with these tools) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 502.6 Td (is recommended.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 474.8 Td (Q: Why do I feel worse before feeling better?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 458.8 Td (As your nervous system begins to regulate, suppressed emotions and body sensations may) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 444.8 Td (surface. This is actually a sign of healing - you're feeling things you've been numb to.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 430.8 Td (Go slowly and seek support if needed.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 403.0 Td (Q: Can children benefit from these tools?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 387.0 Td (Absolutely. Teaching children co-regulation and simple tools like breathing and shaking) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 373.0 Td (helps build nervous system resilience early. Model these practices - children learn) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 359.0 Td (through watching.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 331.2 Td (Q: What is the difference between regulation and relaxation?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 315.2 Td (Relaxation is one state \(parasympathetic\). Regulation is the ability to flexibly move) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 301.2 Td (between states as appropriate - being activated when needed and returning to baseline when) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 287.2 Td (safe.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 259.4 Td (Q: Should I avoid all stress?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 243.4 Td (No. Some stress is healthy and necessary \(exercise, challenges, growth\). The goal is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 229.4 Td (building resilience - the ability to handle stress and recover. Avoid chronic, unrelenting) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 215.4 Td (stress.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 187.6 Td (Q: How do I know if I need professional help?) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 171.6 Td (If dysregulation significantly impacts daily functioning, if you have trauma history, if) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 157.6 Td (you experience dissociation, or if self-help tools aren't providing relief after) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 143.6 Td (consistent practice for 6-8 weeks.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
